esun Airport|Ordu\u2013Giresun]], [[Kansai International Airport|Osaka\u2013Kansai]] (begins 14 April 2020),<ref>https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/284546/turkish-airlines-expands-japan-service-from-april-2020/</ref> [[Oslo Airport, Gardermoen|Oslo\u2013Gardermoen]], [[Ouagadougou Airport|Ouagadougou]], [[Tocumen International Airport|Panama City]], [[Charles de Gaulle Airport|Paris\u2013Charles de Gaulle]], [[Phuket International Airport|Phuket]], [[Podgorica Airport|Podgorica]], [[Agostinho-Neto International Airport|Pointe Noire]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/283572/turkish-airlines-adds-pointe-noire-service-from-july-2019/|title=Turkish Airlines adds Pointe Noire service from July 2019|first=UBM (UK)|last=Ltd. 2019|website=Routesonline}}</ref> [[Port Harcourt International Airport|Port Harcourt]], [[Porto Airport|Porto]], [[Port Sudan New International Airport|Port Sudan]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Turkish Airlines re-schedules Port Sudan launch to late-Feb 2020 |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/283940/turkish-airlines-re-schedules-port-sudan-launch-to-late-feb-2020/ |website=Routesonline}}</ref> [[V\u00e1clav Havel Airport Prague|Prague]], [[Pristina International Airport|Pristina]], [[Riga International Airport|Riga]], [[King Khalid International Airport|Riyadh]], [[Leonardo da Vinci\u2013Fiumicino Airport|Rome\u2013Fiumicino]], [[Platov International Airport|Rostov-on-Don]], [[Pulkovo Airport|Saint Petersburg]], [[Salzburg Airport|Salzburg]], [[Kurumoch International Airport|Samara]], [[Samarkand International Airport|Samarkand]], [[Samsun-\u00c7ar\u015famba Airport|Samsun]], [[San Francisco International Airport|San Francisco]], [[\u015eanl\u0131urfa GAP Airport|\u015eanl\u0131urfa]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo\u2013Guarulhos International Airport|S\u00e3o Paulo\u2013Guarulhos]], [[Sarajevo International Airport|Sarajevo]], [[Incheon International Airport|Seoul\u2013Incheon]], [[Shanghai Pudong International Airport|Shanghai\u2013Pudong]], [[Sharjah International Airport|Sharjah]], [[Sharm El Sheikh International Airport|Sharm El Sheikh]], [[Shiraz International Airport|Shiraz]], [[Singapore Changi Airport|Singapore]], [[Sinop Airport|Sinop]], [[\u015e\u0131rnak Airport|\u015e\u0131rnak]], [[Sivas Airport|Sivas]], [[Skopje International Airport|Skopje]], [[Sochi International Airport|Sochi]], [[Sofia Airport|Sofia]], [[Stockholm\u2013Arlanda Airport|Stockholm\u2013Arlanda]], [[Strasbourg Airport|Strasbourg]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Turkish Airlines schedules Strasbourg launch in late-May 2019 |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/284095/turkish-airlines-schedules-strasbourg-launch-in-late-may-2019/ |website=Routesonline}}</ref> [[Stuttgart Airport|Stuttgart]], [[Sulaymaniyah International Airport|Sulaymaniyah]], [[Tabriz International Airport|Tabriz]], [[Ta'if Regional Airport|Ta'if]], [[Taiwan Taoyuan International Airport|Taipei\u2013Taoyuan]], [[Tallinn Airport|Tallinn]], [[Tashkent International Airport|Tashkent]], [[Tbilisi International Airport|Tbilisi]], [[Imam Khomeini International Airport|Tehran\u2013Imam Khomeini]], [[Ben Gurion Airport|Tel Aviv]], [[Thessaloniki Airport|Thessaloniki]], [[Haneda Airport|Tokyo\u2013Haneda]] (begins 30 March 2020),<ref>{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Turkish Airlines adds Tokyo Haneda service in S20 |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/286941/turkish-airlines-adds-tokyo-haneda-service-in-s20/ |website=Routesonline |accessdate=17 October 2019}}</ref> [[Narita International Airport|Tokyo\u2013Narita]], [[Toronto Pearson International Airport|Toronto\u2013Pearson]], [[Toulouse\u2013Blagnac Airport|Toulouse]], [[Trabzon Airport|Trabzon]], [[Tunis-Carthage International Airport|Tunis]], [[Ufa International Airport|Ufa]], [[Chinggis Khaan International Airport|Ulaanbaatar]], [[U\u015fak Airport|U\u015fak]], [[Valencia Airport|Valencia]], [[Van Airport|Van]], [[Vancouver International Airport|Vancouver]] (begins 9 June 2020),<ref>https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/289347/turkish-airlines-schedules-vancouver-launch-in-june-2020/</ref> [[Varna Airport|Varna]], [[Venice Marco Polo Airport|Venice]], [[Vienna International Airport|Vienna]], [[Vilnius Airport|Vilnius]], [[Voronezh International Airport|Voronezh]], [[Warsaw Chopin Airport|Warsaw\u2013Chopin]], [[Washington Dulles International Airport|Washington\u2013Dulles]], [[Xi'an Xianyang International Airport|Xi'an]], [[Yanbu Airport|Yanbu]], [[Yaound\u00e9 Nsimalen International Airport|Yaound\u00e9]], [[Koltsovo International Airport|Yekaterinburg]], [[Zagreb Airport|Zagreb]], [[Abeid Amani Karume International Airport|Zanzibar]], [[Zaporizhia International Airport|Zaporizhia]], [[Zonguldak Airport|Zonguldak]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Turkish Airlines adds Zonguldak service from May 2019 |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/284327/turkish-airlines-adds-zonguldak-service-from-may-2019/ |website=Routesonline}}</ref> [[Zurich Airport|Z\u00fcrich]] <br /> '''Seasonal:''' [[Friedrichshafen Airport|Friedrichshafen]], [[Karlsruhe/Baden-Baden Airport|Karlsruhe/Baden-Baden]], [[Prince Said Ibrahim International Airport|Moroni]], [[Pisa International Airport|Pisa]], [[Rovaniemi Airport|Rovaniemi]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/281911/turkish-airlines-adds-rovaniemi-service-from-dec-2019/|title=Turkish Airlines adds Rovaniemi service from Dec 2019|first=UBM (UK)|last=Ltd. 2019|website=Routesonline}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n|[[Turkmenistan Airlines]]| [[Ashgabat International Airport|Ashgabat]]\n<!-- -->\n|{{nowrap|[[Ukraine International Airlines]]}} | [[Boryspil International Airport|Kiev\u2013Boryspil]], [[Odessa International Airport|Odessa]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[Uzbekistan Airways]]| [[Samarkand International Airport|Samarkand]], [[Tashkent International Airport|Tashkent]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aviationpros.com/airlines/news/21074393/uzbekistan-airways-to-transfer-all-flights-to-new-istanbul-airport-from-april-7|title=Uzbekistan Airways to Transfer All Flights to New Istanbul Airport from April 7|publisher=Aviation Pros|accessdate=2 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403010513/https://www.aviationpros.com/airlines/news/21074393/uzbekistan-airways-to-transfer-all-flights-to-new-istanbul-airport-from-april-7|archive-date=3 April 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n|[[Zagros Airlines]]| [[Mashhad International Airport|Mashhad]], [[Tehran Imam Khomeini International Airport|Tehran\u2013Imam Khomeini]]\n}}\n\n===Cargo===\nAs of March 2020, there are no regularly scheduled cargo operations at the airport, as they currently still remain at [[Istanbul Atat\u00fcrk Airport]] while extensive cargo handling facilities are to be built at the new airport.\n\n==Statistics==\nBelow is the passenger data and development for Istanbul Airport for the years 2018\u20132020:<ref name=\"dhmi.gov.tr\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dhmi.gov.tr/Lists/IstatistikList/Attachments/367/YOLCU.pdf|title=\u0130statistikler|date=December 2019|website=DHMI|accessdate=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Passenger statistics at Istanbul Airport<ref name=\"dhmi.gov.tr\" />\n! Year\n! Domestic<br /> passengers\n! Passenger<br />% change\n! International<br /> passenger\n! Passenger<br />% change\n! Total<br /> passenger\n! Passenger<br />% change\n! World rank<br /> international\n! World rank<br /> total\n|-\n|2018{{ref|1|1}} || 65,124 ||{{nochange}}|| 30,206 ||{{nochange}}|| 95,330 ||{{nochange}}||{{nochange}}||{{nochange}}\n|-\n|2019 || 12,720,826 ||{{increase}}|| 39,857,182 ||{{increase}}|| 52,578,008 ||{{increase}}||||\n|-\n|2020<br/><small>(Jan)</small><br/> || 1,263,808 ||{{increase}}|| 4,012,452 ||{{increase}}|| 5,276,260 ||{{increase}}||||\n|}\n{{small|{{note|1|1}}: 2018 statistics correspond to the last 3 months of 2018 since the opening of the airport.}}\n\n==Ground transport==\nAlthough currently the airport is only serviced from the city by affordable private Havaist and public [[\u0130ETT]] buses,<ref>{{cite web |title=Public Transport - \u0130GA |url=https://www.istanbulhavalimani.com/en/passenger/transport/public-transport |website=igairport.com |accessdate=6 April 2019}}</ref> it will eventually be linked by two lines of the [[Istanbul Metro]]. The new [[M11 (Istanbul Metro)|M11 line]] starting from [[Gayrettepe (Istanbul Metro)|Gayrettepe station]] is scheduled to open in August 2021. Another from [[Halkal\u0131 railway station|Halkal\u0131]] on the [[Marmaray]] rail line is expected to be completed in 2022.<ref>{{cite web| title = Istanbul airport metro tracklaying begins| date= 21 January 2020|url = https://www.railwaygazette.com/transport-and-mobility-projects/istanbul-airport-metro-tracklaying-begins/55583.article}}</ref>\n\nMainline railway will connect the airport to Halkal\u0131, and via outer city bypass running over the [[Yavuz Sultan Selim Bridge]] across the Bosporus and connecting with the Asian rail network at Gebze.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Istanbul Canal]]\n*[[Otoyol 7|Northern Marmara Motorway]]\n*[[\u00c7anakkale 1915 Bridge]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category-inline}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* [http://www.istanbul-new-airport.com Operator's website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180328153325/http://www.igairport.com/docs/default-source/csed_iga_ana_dokumanlar/b%C3%B6l%C3%BCm-3-planlanan-proje-ve-proje-tan%C4%B1m%C4%B1.pdf Project plan]\n\n{{Portal bar|Turkey|Aviation}}\n{{Airports in Turkey}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Build\u2013operate\u2013transfer]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Istanbul Province]]\n[[Category:Transport infrastructure under construction in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Airports in Istanbul]]\n[[Category:2018 establishments in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Airports established i