\n*''[[Gazeta Sporturilor]]'' [[Romanian Footballer of the Year (Gazeta Sporturilor)|Romanian Footballer of the Year]]: 2014;<ref name=\"RFY_2014\"/> Runner-up 2011\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{RomanianSoccer|1770/lucian-iulian-sanmartean}}\n*{{NFT player|id=5424}}\n*{{WorldFootball.net|lucian-sanmrtean}}\n*{{UEFA player|56262}}\n\n{{Romania squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n{{Romanian Footballer of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sanmartean, Lucian}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Bistri\u021ba]]\n[[Category:Romanian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Romania under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Romania international footballers]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2016 players]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:ACF Gloria Bistri\u021ba players]]\n[[Category:FC Vaslui players]]\n[[Category:FC Steaua Bucure\u0219ti players]]\n[[Category:CS Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu players]]\n[[Category:FC Voluntari players]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:Panathinaikos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:FC Utrecht players]]\n[[Category:Saudi Professional League players]]\n[[Category:Ittihad FC players]]\n[[Category:Al-Taawoun FC players]]\n[[Category:Romanian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Romanian expatriate sportspeople in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Romanian expatriate sportspeople in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Romanian expatriate sportspeople in Saudi Arabia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Lucian S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean\n| image          = LucianSanmartean.jpg\n| image_size     = 220\n| caption        = S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean with [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] in 2007\n| fullname       = Lucian Iulian S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1980|3|13}}\n| birth_place    = [[Bistri\u021ba]], Romania\n| height         = {{height|m=1.76|precision=0}}\n| position       = [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|Attacking midfielder]] / [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| youthyears1    = 1987\u20131998  | youthclubs1  = [[AF Gloria Bistri\u021ba|Gloria Bistri\u021ba]]\n| years1         = 1998\u20132003  | clubs1  = [[AF Gloria Bistri\u021ba|Gloria Bistri\u021ba]]       | caps1 =  89 | goals1 = 12\n| years2         = 2003\u20132007  | clubs2  = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]         | caps2 =  24 | goals2 =  1\n| years3         = 2007\u20132008  | clubs3  = [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]]                       | caps3 =  16 | goals3 =  0\n| years4         = 2009\u20132010  | clubs4  = [[AF Gloria Bistri\u021ba|Gloria Bistri\u021ba]]       | caps4 =  26 | goals4 =  1\n| years5         = 2010\u20132014  | clubs5  = [[FC Vaslui|Vaslui]]                         | caps5 = 121 | goals5 = 11\n| years6         = 2014\u20132015  | clubs6  = [[FC Steaua Bucure\u0219ti|Steaua Bucure\u0219ti]]     | caps6 =  26 | goals6 =  5            \n| years7         = 2015\u20132016  | clubs7  = [[Ittihad FC|Al-Ittihad]]                    | caps7 =  31 | goals7 =  6\n| years8         = 2016\u20132017  | clubs8  = [[CS Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu|Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu]] | caps8 =  17 | goals8 =  2\n| years9         = 2017       | clubs9  = [[Al-Taawoun FC|Al-Taawoun]]                 | caps9 =   8 | goals9 =  0\n| years10        = 2017\u20132018  | clubs10 = [[FC Voluntari|Voluntari]]                   | caps10 =  5 | goals10=  0\n| totalcaps      = 363\n| totalgoals     = 38\n| nationalyears1 = 2000\u20132002 \n| nationalteam1 = [[Romania national under-21 football team|Romania U21]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 12 \n| nationalgoals1   = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2002\u20132016     \n| nationalteam2 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 21 \n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| pcupdate       = {{date|2018-07-05}}\n| ntupdate       = {{date|2016-06-19}}\n}}\n\n'''Lucian Iulian S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean''' (born 13 March 1980) is a Romanian former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] or a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]].\n\nRegarded by coach [[Ioan Sab\u0103u]] as Romania's most talented player after [[Gheorghe Hagi]],<ref name=\"Sanmartean\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://backend.sport.ro/liga-1/sanmartean-la-bistrita-era-cel-mai-talentat-jucator-roman-dupa-hagi.html|title=Sanmartean era cel mai talentat jucator roman dupa Hagi|publisher=Sport.ro|accessdate=8 January 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120707164654/http://backend.sport.ro/liga-1/sanmartean-la-bistrita-era-cel-mai-talentat-jucator-roman-dupa-hagi.html|archivedate=7 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> he has often been praised for his exceptional passes and uncommon dribbling ability,<ref name=\"pase\"/><ref name=\"magician\"/><ref name=\"tehnic\"/> and received the [[Romanian Footballer of the Year]] award in 2014.<ref name=\"RFY_2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gsp.ro/gsp-special/anchetele-gazetei/editie-de-colectie-a-gazetei-iata-laureatii-superlativelor-gsp-2014-tolontan-il-elogiaza-pe-stranierul-anului-440934.html|title=EDI\u0162IE DE COLEC\u0162IE A GAZETEI \u00bb Iat\u0103 laurea\u0163ii Superlativelor GSP 2014! Tolontan \u00eel elogiaz\u0103 pe stranierul anului|trans-title=SPECIAL GAZETA EDITION \u00bb Here are the GSP Superlatives winners for 2014! Tolontan praises the foreigner of the year|newspaper=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=22 December 2014}}</ref> However, much of his career was marked by injuries.\n\nS\u00e2nm\u0103rtean gained his first cap for [[Romania national football team|Romania]] in November 2002, at age 22.\n\n==Club career==\n===Gloria Bistri\u021ba===\nBorn in [[Bistri\u021ba]], S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean started out playing for hometown side [[FC Gloria Progresul Bistri\u021ba|Gloria Bistri\u021ba]], after he was noticed by Constantin Sava.<ref name=\"Sanmartean\">{{cite web|url=http://www.evz.ro/detalii/stiri/sanmartean-povestea-unui-talent-irosit-833637.html|title=Sanmartean, povestea unui talent irosit|publisher=Evenimentul Zilei|accessdate=27 December 2008}}</ref> He joined the Vampires' youth academy at the age of six.<ref name=\"Sanmartean\"/>\n\nS\u0103nm\u0103rtean made his Gloria Bistri\u021ba first-team debut on 24 April 1999 in a 3\u20131 win against FC One\u0219ti as a substitute.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cfgloria.ro/noutate.php?id=169|title=Lucian Sanmartean|date=13 March 2009|publisher=cfgloria.ro|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331120840/http://www.cfgloria.ro/noutate.php?id=169|archivedate=31 March 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He immediately established himself as one of the most talented young players in Romania.<ref name=\"Sanmartean\"/> He helped his team, winning the last [[Cupa Ligii|League Cup]] ever in 2000, scoring in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]]. He also contributed to his team finishing 3rd in [[Divizia A]], highest rank ever, for [[Gloria Bistri\u0163a]].\n\nOn 7 January 2003, the 23-year-old was seen as a straight replacement for former [[FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|Rapid Bucure\u0219ti]] captain [[Constantin Schumacher]] after his departure, media reports suggesting a fee of \u20ac250,000 being paid for S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean.<ref name=\"rapid\">{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=rou/news/newsid=48307.html|title=Rapid snare Sanmartean|date=8 January 2003|publisher=UEFA.com}}</ref> S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean joined Rapid at their winter training camp in Antalya, Turkey, but for reasons which seemed mysterious at the time, he was prevented from playing more than 60 minutes of Rapid's friendly fixtures. On 2 February, he was diagnosed as suffering from type B and type D hepatitis at the Sports Medicine Institute in Bucharest.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=rou/news/newsid=52330.html|title=Hepatitis sidelines Sanmartean|date=3 February 2003|publisher=UEFA.com}}</ref>  However, after his return in Bistri\u0163a, his medical file came clean, the disease being invented, to cover the money disagreement between the two chairmen.<ref name=\"Sanmartean\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/soc-sanmartean-rapidistii-au-pus-doctorul-sa-minta-3782264|title=Rapidistii au pus doctorul sa minta|date=22 January 2009|publisher=prosport.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n===Panathinaikos===\nOn 16 July 2003, [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] confirmed the \u20ac900,000 signing of Romanian international playmaker. The former Romania Under-21 captain signed a three-year contract with the option of a further two years with the Athens club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=82423.html|title=Sanmartean sets sights high|date=13 July 2003|publisher=UEFA}}</ref> S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean became the fifth Romanian at Panathinaikos, after [[Doru Nicolae]], [[D\u0103nu\u021b Lupu]], [[Erik Lincar]] and [[Dumitru Mitu]]. He made his debut for the Greek team on 24 August in a 1\u20130 win against Skoda Xanthi. His first goal came in the [[Greek Cup]], on 17 December against [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI Crete]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://stiri.acasa.ro/sport/cupa-greciei-sanmartean-marcheaza-pentru-panathinaikos-112485.html|title=Sanmartean marcheaza pentru Panathinaikos|date=10 December 2003|publisher=Stiri Acasa|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 14 March, he scored his first and only goal in the [[Superleague Greece|Alpha Ethniki]], against Panionios. In his first season, he won the championship, and the [[Gate 13|Greek fans]] called him \"S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean \u2013 The little magician\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.gr/article/item/215569-magos-me-pelina-podia-pics-vid|script-title=el:\u039c\u03ac\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03c0\u03ae\u03bb\u03b9\u03bd\u03b1 \u03c0\u03cc\u03b4\u03b9\u03b1!|language=Greek|publisher=gazzetta.gr|accessdate=10 August 2011}}</ref> Later he had a conflict with [[Alberto Malesani]] and after no matches in more than two years, S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean was released from his Panathinaikos deal in December 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adevarul.ro/sport/S-a-certat-Malesani_0_41998639.html|title=S-a certat cu Malesani|publisher=adevarul.ro|accessdate=7 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Utrecht===\n[[File:Sanmart.jpg|thumb|left|160px|S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean signing autographs for [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] fans in 2007.]]\nOn 15 February 2007, [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] signed S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean on a short-term contract with the option of a further two years with the Eredivisie club. The Romanian had been expected to undergo a trial with [[AZ Alkmaar]], but he opted for Utrecht.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11920_2405591,00.html|title=Utrecht snap up Sanmartean|date=15 February 2007|publisher=Skysport}}</ref> On completion of the deal, then Utrecht technical director [[Piet Buter]] said of S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean: \"We got ourselves a gold mine. He is a Champions League player, I don't think we'll be able to keep him too long for our team.\"<ref name=\"Sanmartean\"/> On 26 March, he made his unofficial debut, in the [[David Di Tommaso]] Memorial, against [[AS Monaco]], being handed the no. 12 shirt.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/plus/creator-country.php?echipa=1&stire=217|title=Sanmartean a debutat la FC Utrecht|date=26 March 2007|publisher=Romaniansoccer|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 8 April, he was in the startup team against Willem II, counting his [[Eredivisie]] debut.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=199732&cc=5739|title=Utrecht 3\u20130 Willem|date=8 April 2007|publisher=Soccernet}}</ref> On 31 August 2008, Utrecht and S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean decided to end their cooperation, because of his injuries.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.fcutrecht.nl/news/latest/1174/sanmartean-leaves-fc-utrecht|title=Sanmartean leaves FC Utrecht|date=31 August 2008|publisher=fcutrecht.nl|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120709193721/http://en.fcutrecht.nl/news/latest/1174/sanmartean-leaves-fc-utrecht|archivedate=9 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Return to Gloria Bistri\u021ba===\nAfter he became a free agent, S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean started training by himself in Bistri\u021ba.<ref name=\"Sanmartean\"/> On 8 January 2009, he began training with Gloria Bistri\u021ba's first team and on 25 February, he signed a short-term contract with his former team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.realitatea.net/gloria-bistrita--lucian-sanmartean-a-semnat-un-contract-valabil-pe-6-luni_465467.html|title=Lucian Sanmartean a semnat un contract valabil pe 6 luni|date=25 February 2009|publisher=Realitatea|language=Romanian}}</ref> He made his first appearance in his second spell for the club in a league match against Rapid Bucure\u015fti on 1 March, coming on as a substitute and being handed the no. 10 shirt.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.realitatea.net/final-gloria-bistrita-rapid-1-3_467897.html|title=Sanmartean redebuteaza pentru Gloria|date=1 March 2009|publisher=Realitatea|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 10 April, S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean [[Assist (football)|assisted]] Gloria's first, in a 2\u20132 draw against [[CFR Cluj]]. It was his first assist, since his return to Gloria.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.citynews.ro/bistrita-nasaud/sport-9/update-6-cfr-gloria-scor-final-2-2-meci-de-infarct-42368/|title=Meci de infarct|date=10 April 2009|publisher=City News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 23 May, he played his 100 match in Liga I for Gloria Bistri\u0163a.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cfgloria.ro/noutate.php?id=300|title=Sanmartean a jucat meciul 100 in Liga I|date=23 May 2009|publisher=Gloria CF|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331120828/http://www.cfgloria.ro/noutate.php?id=300|archivedate=31 March 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In July, Steaua expressed its interest in the Romanian playmaker, but the disagreement over the player's wage, persuaded him to extend his contract with Gloria.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/dupa-ce-nu-s-a-inteles-cu-steaua-sinmartean-a-revenit-la-gloria-146203.html|title=Dupa ce nu s-a inteles cu Steaua, Sanmartean a revenit la Gloria|date=8 July 2009|publisher=gsp.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 September, S\u0103nm\u0103rtean scored his first goal since December 2004, in a league match against Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u021b.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/ceahlaul-piatra-neamt-gloria-bistrita-scor-2-1-4914434|title=Prima victorie pentru Ceahlaul|date=19 September 2009|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> Following Florin Halagian's appointment, he was given the captain's armband. On 4 October, he obtained his first point since his captain appointment, leading his team to a 1\u20131 draw against [[FC Steaua Bucure\u0219ti|Steaua Bucure\u0219ti]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/steaua-gloria-bistrita-scor-1-1-in-liga-i-4959743|title=Egal in fata ultimei clasate|date=4 October 2009|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 3 December, following a conflict with the team's manager Halagian, Gloria Bistri\u0163a released S\u0103nm\u0103rtean.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/sanmartean-out-de-la-gloria-5148169|title=Sanmartean out de la Gloria|date=2 December 2009|publisher=prosport.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n===Vaslui===\nShortly after, S\u0103nm\u0103rtean signed a 2.5-year contract with the Moldavian team [[FC Vaslui]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vasluifc.ro/stiri-fcvaslui/578-lucian-sanmartean-a-semnat-cu-fc-vaslui.html|title=Lucian Sanmartean a semnat cu FC Vaslui|date=23 December 2009|publisher=Vaslui FC|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331120504/http://www.vasluifc.ro/stiri-fcvaslui/578-lucian-sanmartean-a-semnat-cu-fc-vaslui.html|archivedate=31 March 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 11 February, Vaslui signed his brother, Dinu S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/vasluiul-l-a-luat-si-pe-dinu-sanmartean-lacatus-mai-aduncem-inca-un-fundas-5500628|title=Vasluiul l-a luat si pe Dinu Sanmartean|date=11 February 2009|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 21 February, he made his league debut, against Gaz Metan Media\u015f, being handed the no. 18 shirt.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport.ro/liga-1/vedetele-lui-porumboiu-s-au-impotmolit-la-medias-gaz-metan-0-0-vaslui.html|title=Vedetele lui Porumboiu s-au impotmolit la Medias|date=21 February 2010|publisher=Sport.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 18 March, he provided his first assist, assisting [[Carlo Costly]] for 2\u20131 against Poli Ia\u0219i, from a corner kick.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport.ro/liga-1/acum-live-poli-iasi-0-0-vaslui-vezi-echipele-de-start.html|title=Lacatus se bate iar la titlu|date=18 March 2010|publisher=Sport.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref> Four days later, he played for 19 minutes for the first time alongside his brother for Vaslui, Dinu coming in as a substitute for Hugo Luz in the 53rd minute, and S\u0103nm\u0103rtean being substitute out in the 72nd minute.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport.ro/liga-1/lacatus-salvat-vaslui-1-0-rapid-papp-6.html|title=Lacatus salvat|date=22 March 2009|publisher=Sport.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 15 April, he scored for the first time for his new team, against FC Bra\u015fov in the [[Romanian Cup]], scoring Vaslui's third from a 27-yard free kick. Vaslui went on to win 4\u20130, and secured a spot in the Romanian Cup Final.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.adevarul.ro/locale/brasov/brasov-fc_brasov-fotbal_brasov-cupa_romaniei-semifinale-fc_vaslui_0_244176128.html|title=Vasluiul in finala|date=15 April 2010|publisher=Adevarul|language=Romanian}}</ref> He helped his team finishing third in Liga I, the highest rank ever for Vaslui.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/liga-1/63304/vasluiul-prinde-podiumul-in-urma-victoriei-cu-dinamo.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|title=Vasluiul prinde podiumul|date=22 May 2010|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On 26 May, he was in the startup team against [[CFR Cluj]], in the [[2010 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei Final|Romanian Cup Final]], but he was substituted at half time, due to a minor injury. Vaslui eventually lost the cup in the penalty shootout.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/cupa-romaniei/63485/cfr-cluj-castiga-cupa-si-face-eventul.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|title=CFR castiga cupa|date=27 May 2010|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The [[2009\u201310 FC Vaslui season|2009\u201310 campaign]], represented S\u0103nm\u0103rtean's first season, from the past six years, without any major injury.{{citation needed|date=September 2011}}\n\nThe [[2010\u201311 FC Vaslui season|2010\u201311 season]] started with Vaslui's failed attempt to qualify for the first time in Europa League's Group Stages after being defeated 0\u20132 by French side [[Lille OSC]] in the play-off stage.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-extern/europa-league/fc-vaslui-lille-live-text-de-la-ora-20-00-vezi-echipele-de-start-hazard-rezerva-6952188|title=Vise de marire|date=19 August 2010|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/liga-1/fc-vaslui/66608/vasluiul-scos-din-europa-de-lille.htm|title=Vasluiul scos din Europa de Lille|date=26 August 2010|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On 23 September, he received his first red card since his arrival at the club, in a cup match against ALRO Slatina.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.obiectivdevaslui.ro/?q=node/5397|title=Primul obiectiv ratat|date=23 September 2010|publisher=Obiectivul de Vaslui|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331191705/http://www.obiectivdevaslui.ro/?q=node%2F5397|archivedate=31 March 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He scored his first league goal, with a close range shot against CFR Cluj.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.romanialibera.ro/actualitate/sport/un-meci-nebun-fc-vaslui-cfr-cluj-5-3-202762.html|title=Un meci nebun|date=16 October 2010|publisher=Romania Libera|language=Romanian|access-date=5 September 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101018080552/http://www.romanialibera.ro/actualitate/sport/un-meci-nebun-fc-vaslui-cfr-cluj-5-3-202762.html|archive-date=18 October 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> His second goal came on 1 April 2011, in a 2\u20130 win against [[FC Unirea Urziceni|Unirea Urziceni]]. He scored Vaslui's first with a 17-yard shot just outside the box, maintaining his team in the title chase.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/fc-vaslui-unirea-urziceni-scor-2-0-in-liga-i-8121282|title=Vaslui 2\u20130 Urziceni|date=1 April 2011|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 15 May, he captained Vaslui for the first time, leading his team to a 4\u20132 win in a league match against Sportul Studen\u0163esc.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/de-doi-bani-speranta-fc-vaslui-sportul-studentesc-4-2-8267834|title=De doi bani speranta|date=15 May 2011|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> In his second year at the club, he managed to finish third in Liga I for the second year in a row.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/si-au-respectat-blazonul-pandurii-fc-vaslui-0-1|title=Si-au respectat blazonul|date=23 May 2011|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref> S\u0103nm\u0103rtean was the top assister in Liga I, providing 10 [[Assist (football)|assists]] for his team.<ref name=\"tehnic\">{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/print/fotbal/liga-1/sinmartean-a-fost-cel-mai-tehnic-cassio-cel-mai-precis-geraldo-cel-mai-sigur-de-la-cine-asteptam-superlativele-in-acest-sezon-248563.html|title=Sanmartean cel mai tehnic|date=22 July 2011|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\nAlthough he missed the entire pre-season due to an injury,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/stiri/25247/veste-proasta-pentru-fc-vaslui-sanmartean-rateaza-startul-de-campionat.htm|title=Sanmartean rateaza startul de campionat|date=9 July 2011|publisher=Romanian Soccer|language=Romanian}}</ref> he was a starter against [[FC Rapid Bucure\u015fti|Rapid Bucure\u015fti]], in Vaslui's opening match.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/oscar-cu-sala-goala-rapid-fc-vaslui-3-0-8515615|title=Oscar cu sala goala|date=22 July 2011|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 18 August, in the 2\u20130 victory against [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]], he created the first goal and assisted the second,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-extern/europa-league/vasluiul-ce-minune-fc-vaslui-sparta-praga-2-0-8629483|title=Vasluiul, ce minune!|date=18 August 2011|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> leading his team to a historical qualification in [[2011\u201312 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]'s Group Stages.<ref name=\"magician\">{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/international/europa-league/cifrele-lui-lucian-sinmartean-din-returul-cu-sparta-sint-incredibile-micul-magician-256817.html|title=Cifrele lui Sanmartean din returul cu Sparta sunt incredibile|date=28 August 2011|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 11 September, S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean scored his club's third goal in a 3\u20131 home league victory over [[FC Dinamo Bucuresti|Dinamo Bucuresti]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/i-a-calcat-in-picioare-foto|title=I-a calcat in picioare|date=12 September 2011|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 18 November, S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean signed a new three-year contract with SC Vaslui.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/foto-ana-maria-prodan-a-postat-imagini-de-la-negocierea-contractului-pentru-sinmartean-281424.html|title=Sanmartean si-a prelungit contractul|date=18 November 2011|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 8 December, he received his first personal award, lifting the Midfielder of the Year Award at the Fanatik Awards Ceremony.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/fc-vaslui-echipa-superlativelor|title=FC Vaslui echipa superlativelor|date=9 December 2011|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 19 December, he was awarded the Liga I Footballer of The Year award from [[Liga Profesionist\u0103 de Fotbal|LPF]] and [[Romanian Football Federation|FRF]] at the Romanian Football Ceremony.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/sanmartean-si-wesley-cei-mai-buni-fotbalisti-din-liga-i-nesu-omul-anului-vezi-premiile-oferite-de-lpf-si-frf-9075305|title=S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean \u015fi Wesley, cei mai buni fotbali\u015fti din Liga I! |date=19 December 2011|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 22 December, he finished second on the vote for ''[[Gazeta Sporturilor]]'s'' [[Romanian Footballer of the Year]] Award, behind [[Gabriel Torje]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/gsp-special/anchetele-gazetei/sinmartean-considera-anul-2011-maximumul-carierei-sale-incep-sa-cred-ca-sint-bun-291411.html|title=S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean considera anul 2011 maximul carierei sale |date=22 December 2011|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> He was also voted The Best Romanian Footballer in Liga I by readers of ''[[ProSport]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/sport-life/special/peste-100-000-de-cititori-prosport-au-decis-dan-petrescu-este-antrenorul-anului-bute-sportivul-anului-vezi-toate-premiile-acordate-sportivilor-din-romania-9120328|title=Peste 100 000 de cititori ProSport au decis|date=3 January 2012|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 9 March 2012, he closed the scoreboard in the 4\u20130 home league win against [[Concordia Chiajna]], scoring the fourth goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/fotbal-numele-jocului|title=Fotbal, numele jocului|date=10 March 2012|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 15 March, he assisted three times in the 3\u20132 away victory against [[FC O\u021belul Gala\u021bi|O\u0163elul Gala\u0163i]], helping his team qualifying in the Romanian Cup semi-finals, for the third time in the last four years.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/vasluiul-s-a-calificat|title=Sanmartean a pasat, Vasluiul s-a calificat|date=16 March 2012|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n===Steaua Bucure\u0219ti===\n[[File:Kiev-St (6).jpg|thumb|right|180px|S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean playing for [[FC Steaua Bucure\u0219ti|Steaua Bucure\u0219ti]], October 2014.]]\n\nIn February 2014, S\u0103nm\u0103rtean signed a one-year and a half deal with [[Liga I]] champions [[FC Steaua Bucure\u0219ti|Steaua Bucure\u0219ti]]. He scored on his club debut from a penalty kick in the 44th minute as Steaua won 4\u20130 over Concordia Chiajna.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://stiri.tvr.ro/steaua-concordia-chiajna-4-0-sanmartean-a-inscris-la-debut-doppietta-pentru-chipciu_40473.html\n|title=Steaua-Concordia Chiajna 4-0 / S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean a \u00eenscris la debut|date=14 February 2014|publisher=TVR.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref> He won his first domestic [[2013\u201314 Liga I|league title]] in Romania under the management of [[Lauren\u021biu Reghecampf]] during his first season at the club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fanatik.ro/sanmartean-il-voi-pretui-pina-mor-vrem-eventul-210569|title=S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean a c\u00e2\u015ftigat primul titlu de campion \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|date=8 May 2014|publisher=fanatik.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n===Later years===\nOn 3 January 2015, he signed a contract with [[Ittihad FC|Al-Ittihad]], when he entered his final six months of the deal with [[FC Steaua Bucuresti|Steaua]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enational.ro/sport/sanmartean-a-semnat-cu-al-ittihad-steaua-il-pierde-si-pe-szukala-450425.html/ |title=Sanmartean a semnat cu Al Ittihad. Steaua il pierde si pe Szukala!|publisher=enational.ro|date=4 January 2015|language=Romanian}}</ref> The two clubs reached an agreement to release the player before his contract with Steaua ended, thus he joined Al-Ittihad in January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.agerpres.ro/sport/2015/01/14/fotbal-steaua-se-desparte-de-szukala-si-sanmartean-00-02-13 |title=Fotbal: Steaua se desparte de Szukala \u0219i S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean |publisher=[[Agerpres]] |date=14 January 2015|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 November 2017 he announced his football return after signing with [[FC Voluntari]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digisport.ro/Sport/FOTBAL/Competitii/Liga+1/Telenovela+Sanmartean+s-a+incheiat+Semneaza+azi+si+poate+juca+in/ |title=OFICIAL! S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean a semnat cu FC Voluntari. Durata contractului \u0219i prima reac\u021bie a lui Lucian|publisher=Digi Sport.ro|date=22 November 2017|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nThe former [[Romania national under-21 football team|Romania U-21]] captain,<ref name=\"rapid\"/> earned his first cap in an exhibition match against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] on 20 November 2002.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.adevarul.ro/sport/Ne-am-impiedicat-Croatia_0_82793025.html|title=Ne-am impiedicat din nou de Croatia|date=21 November 2002|publisher=Adevarul|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024021834/http://www.adevarul.ro/sport/Ne-am-impiedicat-Croatia_0_82793025.html|archivedate=24 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Because of the hepatitis rumours he lost for a few months the national team, but he was recalled for the friendly against [[Lithuania national football team|Lithuania]]. On 23 May 2011, he was recalled for the [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying Group D|Euro 2012 qualifying]] match against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref name=\"Nationala\">{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/nationala/sanmartean-revine-la-nationala-dupa-8-ani-toate-bucuriile-au-venit-tarziu-la-mine-8300229|title=Sanmartean revine la nationala dupa 8 ani|date=1 June 2011|publisher=prosport.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref> However, following [[Victor Piturca]]'s appointment as Romanian national team's coach, S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean was not called for the friendly against [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]], despite his good shape.<ref name=\"pase\">{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/nationala/porumboiu-sinmartean-este-un-fotbalist-stralucitor-nu-inteleg-de-ce-nu-e-convocat-la-nationala-252850.html|title=Sanmartean e un fotbalist stralucitor, nu inteleg de ce nu e chemat la nationala|date=14 August 2011|publisher=GSP|language=Romanian}}</ref> The Romanian fans started a petition called \"S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean at the National team\" on [[Facebook]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.facebook.com/pages/Petitie-pentru-convocarea-lui-Lucian-Sanmartean-la-Nationala/143524232398436|title=Petitie pentru convocarea lui Lucian Sanmartean la Nationala|publisher=facebook.com|accessdate=7 September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/nationala/sinmartean-convocat-la-nationala-de-fani-254629.html|title=Sanmartean convocat la nationala de fani|date=20 August 2011|publisher=gsp.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref> but it had no effect because he was not included in the squad once again.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/milanov-la-nationala-bulgariei-sanmartean-uitat-de-piturca|title=Sanmartean uitat de Piturca|date=30 August 2011|publisher=vrn.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref> Nevertheless, Lucian was called up for the qualifying matches vs. Belarus and Albania in October 2011. He was also called up for [[UEFA Euro 2016|Euro 2016]] in France, making one appearance as Romania were eliminated in the group stage.\n\nHe officially announced his retirement from the national team on 13 June 2017 before Romania's match against [[Chile national football team|Chile]].\n\n::''Scores and results table. Romania's goal tally first:''\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|'''International appearances and goals'''\n|-\n! App !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Result !! Goal !! Competition\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|'''2002\u20132003'''\n|-\n| 1. || 20 November 2002 || [[Timi\u015foara]], [[Romania]] || {{Fb|CRO}} || 0\u20131 || 0 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 2. || 30 April 2003 || [[Kaunas]], [[Lithuania]] || {{Fb|LIT}} || 1\u20130 || 0 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|'''2003\u201304'''\n|-\n| 3. || 20 August 2003 || [[Donetsk]], [[Ukraine]] || {{Fb|UKR}} || 2\u20130 || 0 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|'''2010\u201311'''\n|-\n| 4. || 3 June 2011 || [[Bucure\u015fti]], [[Romania]] || {{Fb|BIH}} || 3\u20130 || 0 || [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying Group D|UEFA Euro 2012 qualification]]\n|-\n| 5. || 8 June 2011 || [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]] || {{Fb|BRA}} || 0\u20131 || 0 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 6. || 12 June 2011 || [[Asunci\u00f3n]], [[Paraguay]] || {{Fb|PRY}} || 0\u20132 || 0 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 7. || 7 October 2011 || [[Bucure\u015fti]], [[Romania]] || {{Fb|BLR}} || 2\u20132 || 0 || [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying Group D|UEFA Euro 2012 qualification]]\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|'''2014\u201315'''\n|-\n| 8. || 11 October 2014 || [[Bucure\u015fti]], [[Romania]] || {{Fb|HUN}} || 1\u20131 || 0 || [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group F|UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]\n|-\n| 9. || 14 October 2014 || [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]] || {{Fb|FIN}} || 2\u20130 || 0 || [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group F|UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]\n|-\n| 10. || 14 November 2014 || [[Bucure\u015fti]], [[Romania]] || {{Fb|NIR}} || 2\u20130 || 0 || [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group F|UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]\n|-\n| 11. || 18 November 2014 || [[Bucure\u015fti]], [[Romania]] || {{Fb|DEN}} || 2\u20130 || 0 ||  [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 12. || 29 March 2015 || [[Ploie\u0219ti]], [[Romania]] || {{Fb|FRO}} || 1\u20130 || 0 || [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group F|UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|'''2015\u201316'''\n|-\n| 13. || 4 September 2015 || [[Budapest]], [[Hungary]] || {{Fb|HUN}} || 0\u20130 || 0 || [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group F|UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]\n|-\n| 14. || 7 September 2015 || [[Bucure\u015fti]], [[Romania]] || {{Fb|GRE}} || 0\u20130 || 0 || [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group F|UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\nOn 27 July 2010, he became a father for the first time when his ex-wife gave birth to a girl, whom they named Natalia. [http://m.cancan.ro/casanova-sanmartean-recidiveaza-avem-stenogramele-flirtului-dintre-magicianul-lui-gigi-ci-o-sexy-siliocnata.html]\n\nHis younger brother [[Dinu S\u0103nm\u0103rtean|Dinu]] was also a professional footballer. They have played together for both [[Gloria Bistri\u0163a]] and [[SC Vaslui]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/fundasul-dinu-sanmartean-a-plecat-de-la-gloria-bistrita-5474408|title=Funda\u015ful Dinu S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean a plecat de la Gloria Bistri\u0163a|publisher=mediafax.ro|language=Romanian |trans-title=Defender Dinu S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean left Gloria Bistrita|accessdate= 8 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cancan.ro/sanmartean-din-liga-1-in-liga-a-saptea-cand-nu-este-pe-teren-petrece-8-ore-pe-zi-intr-o-fabrica.html|title=Sanmartean din Liga 1 in liga a saptea! Cand nu este pe teren, petrece 8 ore pe zi intr-o fabrica!|publisher=cancan.ro|language=Romanian |trans-title=Sanmartean from the Liga 1 to the seventh league! When not in the field, he spends 8 hours a day in a factory!|accessdate= 8 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Club\n! rowspan=2 | Season\n! colspan=3 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Continental\n! colspan=2 | Other\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Division\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=7|[[ACF Gloria 1922 Bistri\u0163a|Gloria Bistri\u0163a]]||[[1998\u201399 Divizia A|1998\u201399]]||rowspan=6|[[Liga I|Divizia A]]||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||1||0\n|-\n|[[1999\u20132000 Divizia A|1999\u201300]]||9||0||2||0||2||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||13||1\n|-\n|[[2000\u201301 Divizia A|2000\u201301]]||26||2||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=2|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||28||2\n|-\n|[[2001\u201302 Divizia A|2001\u201302]]||27||3||2||1||colspan=2|\u2013||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||30||4\n|-\n|[[2002\u201303 Divizia A|2002\u201303]]||26||7||1||0||colspan=2|\u2013||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||30||7\n|-\n|[[2003\u201304 Divizia A|2003\u201304]]||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||3||3||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||3||3\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!89||12||7||1||2||1||7||3||0||0||105||17\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]||[[Alpha Ethniki 2003\u201304|2003\u201304]]||rowspan=2|[[Superleague Greece|Alpha Ethniki]]||18||1||4||1||rowspan=2 colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||4||0||rowspan=2 colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||26||2\n|-\n|[[Alpha Ethniki 2004\u201305|2004\u201305]]||6||0||0||0||1||1||7||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!24||1||4||1||0||0||5||1||0||0||33||3\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]]||[[Eredivisie 2006\u201307|2006\u201307]]||rowspan=3|[[Eredivisie]]||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|